message: It is still many years before Frodo’s journey will begin...
Frodo is still living in the Shire before his journey begins
Frodo has begun his journey, heading eastward from Bag End with Sam and Pippin.
Frodo, Sam, and Pippin are trekking through the Woody End, encountering Black Riders and Gildor’s Elves.
Frodo, Sam, and Pippin take a shortcut through Maggot’s Farm and cross the Brandywine River with Merry.
Frodo, Sam, Merry, and Pippin are negotiating the Old Forest.
Frodo, Sam, Merry, and Pippin are resting in the house of Tom Bombadil.
reading_chapter_title: In the House of Tom Bombadil

message: Frodo, Sam, Merry, and Pippin are taken captive by a Barrow-wight while crossing the Barrow Downs.
Frodo, Sam, Merry, and Pippin, having been rescued from the Barrow-wight by Tom Bombadil, reach The Prancing Pony in Bree.
reading_chapter_title: At the Sign of The Prancing Pony

message: Strider is leading Frodo, Sam, Merry, and Pippin northward from Bree into the Chetwood.
Frodo, Sam, Merry, Pippin, and Strider are passing from the Chetwood into the Midgewater Marshes.
Having reached the end of the Midgewater Marshes, Frodo, Sam, Merry, Pippin, and Strider are making their way toward Weatherop.
Camping beneath Weathertop, Frodo, Sam, Merry, Pippin, and Strider are attacked by the Ringwraiths.
With Frodo wounded, Frodo, Sam, Merry, Pippin, and Strider are hurrying eastward toward the River Hoarwell.
With Frodo wounded, Frodo, Sam, Merry, Pippin, and Strider are crossing over the Last Bridge into the Trollshaws.
With Frodo wounded, Frodo, Sam, Merry, Pippin, and Strider are traversing the hills of the Trollshaws.
Frodo, Sam, Merry, Pippin, and Strider encounter Bilbo’s trolls, and are found by Glorfindel.
Glorfindel is leading Frodo, Sam, Merry, Pippin, and Strider to the Ford of Bruinen.
Frodo, Sam, Merry, Pippin, Strider, and Glorfindel escape the Ringwraiths over the Ford of Bruinen, and are brought to Rivendell.
Frodo is receiving healing for the Morgul-knife wound from Elrond in Rivendell.
Frodo has awoken in Rivendell, and is reunited with his companions, Gandalf, and Bilbo in the Last Homely House.
At the Council of Elrond, Frodo declares he is willing to take the Ring to Mordor.
Frodo is resting in the Last Homely House, awaiting word from scouts before he can leave Rivendell.
Frodo is appointed along with the Fellowship of the Ring by Elrond to take the Ring to Mordor.
Frodo is preparing to leave Rivendell, and receives Sting and the mithril-coat from Bilbo.
Frodo and the Fellowship are setting forth from Rivendell.
Frodo and the Fellowship are heading south along the Misty Mountains.
Frodo and the Fellowship are travelling through Hollin toward the Redhorn Pass.
Frodo and the Fellowship are ascending the Redhorn Pass beneath Mount Caradhras.
Frodo and the Fellowship are turned back from the Redhorn Pass by snowstorms.
Frodo and the Fellowship are attacked by Wolves and the Watcher in the Water, and pass through the West-gate into Moria.
Frodo and the Fellowship are passing through the Mines of Moria and reach the Twenty-first Hall.
Gandalf having fallen with the Balrog at the Bridge of Khazad-dûm, Frodo and the Fellowship escape Moria and meet Haldir’s Elves by the River Nimrodel.
Haldir is leading Frodo and the Fellowship through Lothlórien toward Caras Galadhon.
Frodo and the Fellowship are welcomed into Caras Galadhon.
Frodo and the Fellowship are resting in Lórien.
Frodo and Sam look into the Mirror of Galadriel.
Frodo and the Fellowship bid farewell to Lórien, taking boats down the Great River.
Frodo and the Fellowship are rowing down the Great River.
Frodo and the Fellowship’s boats are attacked by Orcs as they reach the rapids of Sarn Gebir.
Frodo and the Fellowship pass the Argonath and reach Parth Galen.
The Fellowship breaks; Frodo and Sam cross to the eastern shore of the Great River, passing into the eastern Emyn Muil.
Frodo and Sam are traversing eastward over the Emyn Muil.
Frodo and Sam descend the Emyn Muil and encounter Gollum.
Gollum leads Frodo and Sam out of the Emyn Muil and into the Dead Marshes.
Gollum is leading Frodo and Sam over the Dead Marshes.
Frodo, Sam, and Gollum reach the slag-mounds on the edge of the Desolation of the Morannon.
Frod and, Sam attempt to enter Mordor by the Morannon, the Black Gate, but Gollum tells them of another way.
Frodo, Sam, and Gollum are heading south through Ithilien.
Frodo and Sam are taken by Faramir to Henneth Annûn.
Frodo, Sam, and Gollum leave Henneth Annûn, heading south.
Frodo, Sam, and Gollum reach the Morgul-road, and turn eastward to the Cross-roads.
Frodo, Sam, and Gollum reach the Cross-roads, entering the Morgul vale.
Frodo, Sam, and Gollum are climbing the Stairs of Cirith Ungol.
Frodo and Sam are led by Gollum into Shelob’s Lair.
Poisoned by Shelob, Frodo is taken captive by the Orcs of Cirith Ungol.
Sam rescues Frodo from the Tower of Cirith Ungol.
